{{Frame
|Name gloss=educational deprivation
|Description=systematic depriv. of education
|Other aliases=منع از تحصیل
|Comments=This frame broadly corresponds with Access to education, but is most precisely about being denied educational opportunities. Please advise. This frame is similar to the following         محروم شدن از فرصت های تحصیلی:frame in the Persian Wiki 
|Family=طرح های دسترسی به تحصیلات
|Cultural information=In modern day Iran, various groups--ethnic, religious and ideological--have been deprived from secondary or higher education by the regime. These groups include the Baha'is of Iran--the biggest religious minority in the country--Afghan residents of Iran--most of whom fled Afghanistan following the Soviet occupation of their country in 1979--as well as ethnic "minorities" of Iran--Kurdish, . Arab, Baluchi--who are deprived of education due to poverty, unemployment and language barrier (native language is spoken at home until students enter the educational system exclusively taught in standard Persian). Reports suggest that more than 50 percent of Arab-Iranians drop out of high school
